==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic: cognate with Old Frisian [[aka|āka]], Old Saxon [[okian|ōkian]], Old Norse [[auka]], Gothic [[𐌰𐌿𐌺𐌰𐌽]].  From the same Indo-European source as Latin [[augere]], Greek [[αυχειν]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'æ:akan/

===Verb===
'''ēacan''' (class VII strong)
# to be increased or enlarged
#:''Heo wæs mago-timbre be Abrahame eacen worden'': she was increased with offspring by Abraham.

===Descendants===
*English [[eke]]
*Scots [[eik]]

